The paper discusses the use of deep learning for navigation, which is a topic that falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The paper specifically focuses on vision-based navigation, which suggests that it may also fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep learning also suggests that it may fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the integration of deep learning into a full navigation pipeline, which suggests that it may also fall under the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
